cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper deals with the problem of integrating Monocular SLAM with trajectory planning frameworks, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses Reinforcement Learning (RL) to generate fail-safe trajectories, which involves training a neural network to learn the complex relation between perceptual inputs and motor actions. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of ensuring that the SLAM generated outputs do not deviate largely from their true values, which is a control problem. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
